Events.Text: Say hallo to the AI Assistant. [instruction 1 of 6]
Hallo!
Hello. How can I help you?
Hello, how can I help?
My name is Ben and I would like to schedule a viewing at the North Hill Apartments.
You suddenly remember that you have a friend's wedding on Saturday at 9 pm. [instruction 2 of 6]
What day would you like to view?
What day would you like to make the booking for?
I wanted to do it on Saturday at 9 PM, but I just remembered I have to go to a wedding that time.
Ask something about the apartment, or engage in smalltalk, or make a joke. [instruction 3 of 6]
Alright. Is there a different day and time that you prefer?
Alright. Is there a different day and time that you prefer?
I have to check my schedule. I heard that this apartment is near some restaurants, is that right?

You cannot remember if you had payed the application fee. Find a way to make an appointment anyway. If no date is available, change date and/or time until something works. If you already got the appointment, engage in smalltalk. [instruction 4 of 6]
I'm sorry. I don't understand.
I am sorry, I don't quite understand what you mean. I am only able to help you book apartment viewings.
Oh well. Check if the apartment is free on Sunday at 10 am.
Once you've scheduled the viewing, say something about your friend's wedding. [instruction 5 of 6]
Have you paid the application fee?
Have you already paid the application fee for the apartment?
Actually I'm not sure. I have to find the receipt, but if I haven't can I just pay for it there? Hopefully I won't be too hungover from my friend's wedding.
When you are done with all the instructions, bring the conversation to a natural close.  [instruction 6 of 6]
Do you have custom message?
Would you like to add a message for the letting agency?
No not really. Can I view the apartment on Sunday at 10 am?
